The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           IN THE CITY
                  
	 Kalighat were in control at the end of the second days play against Bhowanipore in the second semi-final of the A.N. Ghosh Trophy on Saturday. In reply to Kalighats 534, Bhowanipore were reeling at 155 for five.      
	Brief scores: Kalighat 534 (Md Ziauddin 212, R Banerjee 143). Bhowanipore 155/5 (M Lodhgar 2/26). Match to continue.          
	 Bhukailash Sporting thrashed Indian Boys Athletic Club by 10 wickets to win the CAB second division league title on Saturday. They, thus, have confirmed their berth in the first division next season.      
	Brief Scores: IBAC 255/9 (Atanu Chakraborty 75, Pankaj Thakur 5/97). Bhukailash Sptg 256/0 (Sufian Khan 124 n.o., Ritesh Jaiswal 119 n.o.). Bhukailash won by 10 wkts.                
	 Sadhan Dutta will represent India in the forthcoming World Veterans Table Tennis Championship in Rio de Janeiro from May 24. He will participate in the 50-60 age-group. This is the fourth time the veteran player will take part in the tournament.                
	 The IFAs annual general meeting has been postponed for the time being and will be held before June 30.                
	CRICKET: A.N. Ghosh Trophy semi-final: Kalighat vs Bhowanipore (9.30 am)                                                                                                                                                                     
